  "text": "Medicinal plants have been used from the very beginning in health care systems. Studies have been carried out globally to verify their efficacy and some of the findings have led to the production of plant-based medicines. Due to limited access to modern medicine, the local population uses medicinal plants to treat most diseases [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Recent focus on plant research has increased worldwide and most evidence has been collected to determine the immense potential of medicinal plants [CITATION_3] . Medical plants have therapeutic benefits and fewer side effects in comparison with synthetic drugs [CITATION_4] . Drugs used for neurological diseases along with their side effects are given in (Table 2) .",
